AGI - Hungarian judge Josef Szos unveiled during the process in Budapest the address of the house where Ilaria Salis is located at the domiciles after the scarceness. Legal sources report it. "The revelation was received by a Mormon in the classroom and by the protests of our Hungarian colleague and Roberto Salis - explains to AGI lawyer Mauro Straini -. Only after the complaints the judge ordered to cancel the address from the record and not to disclose it to journalists but now the damage had been done".
&nbsp;
The Italian Ambassador to Hungary Manuel Jacoangeli, during the hearing in court &nbsp; asked for the intervention of the two security experts of the State Police assigned to the embassy. "As a result of the disclosure of the address of Ilaria Salis by the judge we immediately made a note to the Hungarian authorities, reporting what happened and requesting the adoption of all the necessary measures to ensure safety. I also asked my colleagues officials of the State Police to act with their Hungarian contacts to check the maximum attention to the case."
<h2> Prorogation of precautionary custody
Judge Szos extended for another six months the custody in Hungary against the woman. "In fact, he dismissed our repeated request to have her domiciled in Italy," explains lawyer Mauro Straini present at the hearing with his colleague Eugenio Losco. The defendant arrived in the courtroom and went away aboard a taxi accompanied by the father and the lawyers. Homeowners have no limitations on receiving people. The process was updated on September 6.&nbsp;
&nbsp;
Two witnesses and a alleged victim summoned by the judge did not recognize Ilaria Salis in the process in Budapest in which he is accused of having assaulted militants of extreme right during a countermanifestation in the 'Honour Day', a re-evocation of tribute to the philanthropist fighters, still reports Straini: "No one of the three, two women, and one man, recognized her, urged by the judge to say if they saw her in those fringes. One of the victims said he had realized three months after the fact of having three ribs in addition to the others already indicated in the chief of the defendant. He couldn't explain why he waited so long to get them to refer but he said he continued to practice archery in these months."
&nbsp;
For the first time since the debate began, the Milanese teacher presented himself without leashes or chains having been discarded. As ordered by the court of second instance, he wore the electronic bracelet. The victim of the attack, Zoltan Toth, said he was hit with kicks and handed over by a group of people who had the masked face and therefore could not recognize any of them.&nbsp;

